Description: Plastic box (with yellow label '71') with transparent lid containing a mass of crumpled papyrus. A label by Stephen Quirke reads 'Fragments (black?); clump of mud with Coptic (?or Greek) papyrus. Stored back of Pap. Room (15/1/92)'. The fragments inside are unmounted and unglazed.
Curator's comments: Previously unregistered material stored in Papyrus Store.
